    <h2>Continuous Integration & Continuous Delivery (CI/CD)</h2>
    <p>
      Azure DevOps provides a complete ecosystem to automate, build, test, and deploy applications at scale. CI/CD pipelines help ensure reliability, speed, and consistency across development and production environments.
    </p>

    <h3>Build Pipelines</h3>
    <p>
      Build pipelines handle code compilation, dependency installation, running automated tests, and generating build artifacts. Developers commit code, and the pipeline triggers automatically to validate changes.
    </p>

    <h3>Release Pipelines</h3>
    <p>
      Release pipelines deploy validated builds to environments such as Dev, QA, UAT, and Production. Stages can include approvals, automated testing, and environment-specific configurations.
    </p>

    <h3>Creating Pipelines</h3>
    <p>
      Azure DevOps allows pipeline creation using YAML or the classic UI editor. Pipelines can be fully automated and integrated with repositories like GitHub or Azure Repos to enable smooth DevOps workflows.
    </p>
